Diabetes UK aims to link to websites that provide relevant and useful
information for people living with diabetes, healthcare professionals and
We only link to websites that fulfil the criteria outlined in our policy for
inclusion of links. This policy has been written in accordance with Diabetes
Please send any links requests to Supporter Services which will forward it to
the most appropriate team. Processing your requests may take up to six weeks.
## If you would like to insert a link to our site from yours
We generally have no objection to other sites inserting text links to our
site, provided there is no suggestion that we are endorsing your site.
Including our logo on your site, however, would require separate permission.
## If you would like to reproduce our logo on your site
The website team passes on such requests to the relevant departments within
Diabetes UK for vetting. Requests from corporate websites must be agreed by
our Partnerships team. For all other requests, our marketing team will
consider the co-branding implications before permission can be granted.
Please email the Website Manager atwebsite@diabetes.org.ukwith your details
and information about your website. Processing your requests may take up to
